---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Kari-Out — Customer Story — Formic"
  description="Kari-Out automated palletizing at its Totowa, NJ plant with no CapEx — 25% more output, 100% uptime, and zero workers' comp claims on the floor's highest-turnover job."
  ogTitle="Kari-Out — Formic Customer Story"
  ogDescription="25% more output · 100% uptime · zero CapEx"
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/stories/kari-out" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/stories">Customer Stories</a><span class="sep">/</span>Kari-Out
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Customer Story · Kari-Out</div>
    <h1 style="font-size:clamp(32px,3.8vw,56px)">25% More Output, Zero Stress: How Kari-Out Automated Palletizing Without CapEx</h1>
    <p class="lede">Kari-Out put robotic palletizers on its Totowa, New Jersey floor — and turned the plant's highest-turnover job into 25% more output, 100% uptime, and zero workers' comp claims, with no capital outlay.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <img src="/stories/kari-out-hero.jpg" alt="Kari-Out palletizing operation" />
      <span class="dv-cap">Kari-Out · Totowa, New Jersey</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:64px 0 0">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 80px">
    <div class="db-tag">At a glance</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(150px,1fr));gap:1px;background:var(--lgrey);border:1px solid var(--lgrey);margin-top:14px">
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">In business</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">60 years</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Location</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Totowa, NJ</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Industry</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Foodservice disposables</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Plant size</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">~1M sq ft</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Plant team</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">~170 employees</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — The Challenge</div>
      <h2>The highest-turnover job <em>on the floor</em>.</h2>
      <p>At Kari-Out's Totowa, New Jersey facility, 18 people ran palletizing — physically punishing work that drove 130% annual turnover, cycling 225 workers through a 170-person plant in a single year. Upstream production outpaced downstream capacity, and the resulting slowness and errors triggered customer complaints and occasional fines. Director of Manufacturing Peter Santo Rodriguez knew robots could eliminate the mistakes, but building automation in-house meant expertise and capital he wanted to spend elsewhere.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>130% annual turnover — 225 workers cycled in one year</li>
        <li>18 people tied up on the plant's hardest task</li>
        <li>Errors driving customer complaints and fines</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0095.jpg" alt="Robotic palletizer taking on the high-strain stacking task" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Palletizing · automated</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Formic Full Service palletizing cell" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Pay for outcomes</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — The Solution</div>
      <h2>Paying for outcomes, <em>not headaches</em>.</h2>
      <p>Peter wanted certainty and consistency, not just equipment — reliable operations and his team's attention freed for higher-value work. Formic's model delivered exactly that: automation deployed with no capital and no internal maintenance burden. The first system went in during November; minor startup issues were resolved fast through hands-on support, and the results were strong enough that Kari-Out ordered six more identical palletizing robots.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Zero CapEx, zero internal maintenance overhead</li>
        <li>Responsive, hands-on support through startup</li>
        <li>Six more identical robots ordered after launch</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:88px 80px">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0">
    <div class="pull-quote">
      <blockquote>"If I didn't see the outcome firsthand, I wouldn't believe you. When you hear that you can deploy automation without capital and without internal maintenance, that doesn't sound real. But it's real. It's attainable."</blockquote>
      <cite>Peter Santo Rodriguez · Director of Manufacturing, Kari-Out</cite>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px;text-align:center">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:center">03 — The Outcome</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(40px,5vw,72px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1;color:var(--white);margin:18px 0 56px">25% more output. <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">Zero stress.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1)">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">25%</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">More output</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">100%</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Uptime since deploy</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">6</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">More robots ordered</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Automation without <em>the headaches</em>.</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/stories" class="btn-ctawh">More Customer Stories</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
